<ol>
  <li>Write the following python code. I tested it on python 2.x. I think on python 3.x will run  too.</li>
</ol>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>[root@test crazytests]# cat simple_https.py
import BaseHTTPServer, SimpleHTTPServer
import ssl


httpd = BaseHTTPServer.HTTPServer(('new.test.my', 4443), SimpleHTTPServer.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler)

httpd_soccet = ssl.wrap_socket(httpd.socket, keyfile="testkey.pem", certfile='testcert.pem', server_side=True)

httpd.serve_forever()
[root@test crazytests]#
</code></pre></div></div>
